    {
      "id": "RQ-0052",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Apply Rust 1.95 library APIs where they reduce unsafe or mutation boilerplate",
      "description": "Audit Ralph's Rust code for focused, value-positive adoption of Rust 1.95's newly stabilized library APIs. Prioritize APIs that simplify real code: `Vec::push_mut` / `insert_mut`, `VecDeque::*_mut`, atomic `update` / `try_update`, `cfg_select!`, `core::hint::cold_path`, `bool: TryFrom<{integer}>`, const `ControlFlow` helpers, and the `MaybeUninit`/`Cell` array conversion accessors. Replace older patterns only when the result is clearer, safer, or measurably better.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "rust",
        "refactor",
        "quality",
        "clippy"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/lock/acquisition.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/webhook/",
        "crates/ralph/src/runutil/",
        "crates/ralph/src/runner/",
        "crates/ralph/src/queue/",
        "crates/ralph/tests/",
        "cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings",
        "cargo test"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "Rust 1.95.0 stabilized `Vec::push_mut`, `Vec::insert_mut`, `VecDeque` mutating insertion helpers, atomic `update`/`try_update`, `cfg_select!`, `core::hint::cold_path`, multiple `MaybeUninit`/`Cell` array accessors, `bool: TryFrom<{integer}>`, and const `ControlFlow::{is_break,is_continue}`.",
        "Repository search found atomic counters in lock and webhook-related tests and many push-after-construct patterns that may benefit from `push_mut` only if mutation immediately follows insertion.",
        "Ralph's file-scope standards require clear, simple code; new APIs should be adopted only where they reduce boilerplate or safety risk."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Search for insert-then-mutate, push-then-last_mut, fetch_update/compare_exchange loops, cfg-heavy platform branches, and cold error-path helpers across `crates/ralph/src` and tests.",
        "Convert only candidates where Rust 1.95 APIs improve clarity, remove duplicated atomic retry loops, or reduce unsafe/manual initialization surface.",
        "Avoid introducing unchecked pointer APIs unless there is already proven unsafe code that becomes clearer and remains justified.",
        "Add or update targeted regression tests for any behavior touched by refactors and run formatting, clippy, and tests."
      ],
      "notes": [
        "Do not force `MaybeUninit`, `Cell`, or pointer APIs into safe code that does not need them.",
        "If no strong candidates exist, record that result in the stack audit instead of making low-value churn."
      ],
